**Definition**
Data attributes in jQuery Mobile are custom HTML attributes (starting with `data-`) used to define UI behavior, widget roles, themes, and configurations directly within markup.

**Types**

* `data-role` (identifies widgets like page, header, listview)
* `data-theme` (applies color themes)
* `data-transition` (page transitions)
* `data-icon` (icons for buttons)
* `data-inset`, `data-mini`, etc. (layout controls)

**Working**
jQuery Mobile scans HTML elements on page load and converts elements with data attributes into enhanced mobile UI widgets.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
HTML Element → data-role="button" → Mobile Button Rendered
```

**Advantages**

* No JavaScript required for UI setup
* Clean, declarative markup
* Quick prototyping
* Consistent behavior across devices

**Disadvantages**

* Limited customization
* Too many attributes can clutter HTML

**Examples**

```html
<a href="#" data-role="button" data-icon="home" data-theme="b">
  Home
</a>
```

**Short code snippets**

```html
<div data-role="page" data-theme="a">
```

**Applications**

* UI components creation
* Page navigation
* Theming
* Layout control in mobile web apps
